c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Hive is best suited for marketing teams, mid size companies, collaborative teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Notion AI, meanwhile, shines for knowledge workers, startups, content teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2015, Hive describes itself as \"AI-enhanced project management platform with flexible views and team tools.\" Notion AI, established in 2013, positions itself as \"AI-powered workspace combining notes, docs, tasks, and databases.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Notion AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Hive is a poor choice — far from it. Hive excels in its own right, particularly for marketing teams and mid size companies.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value incredibly flexible all-in-one workspace, go with Notion AI. If flexible project views matters more to you, Hive is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
